CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 3, 1956, pg. A24, reads: "Diggin' the Platters - Record hops really 'stone' high school students these days, so it' quite easy to see why Schenleyites would be 'in style.'  Left to right: 'Ed' Lucenti, president of the senior class; Elaine Liuck [Luick], social committee chairman of the student board; Frances LeDonne, social committee chairman of the senior class, and Ralph Proctor, president of the senior class; Elaine Luick, social gin' the spinning platters during the Barry Kaye record hop at the school, recently. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School students "Ed" Lucenti, Elaine Luick, Frances LeDonne, and Ralph Proctor posed with envelope
